snippet.title: SpaceX Starship Flight 9
snippet.description:
The first launch attempt for Starship Flight 9 with Booster 14-2 and Ship 35 from Pad A, Starbase, Earth. The window for the launch opens at 18:30 local time (23:30 UTC) on Tuesday, May 27. 

This mission will not include a catch of Booster 14, as the Booster will splashdown in the Gulf. Ship 35 will be the focus of this test flight, as SpaceX aims to perform a successful SECO with the upgraded Block 2 version, follow two consecutive flights which failed to reach that milestone.

Ship 35 is the third Block 2 Ship, featuring several upgrades to mitigate the problems suffered during Flights 7 and 8.

⚡ Become a member of NASASpaceflight's channel for exclusive discord access, fast turnaround clips, and other exclusive benefits. Your support helps us continue our 24/7 coverage. ⚡

snippet.title: Townsville Blackhawks vs PNG Hunters| Match Highlights| Hostplus Cup 2025
snippet.description:
PNG Hunters have lost their Round 10 clash to Townsville Blackhawks 36 - 26 this evening at the Jack Manski Oval, Townsville, Australia.
The Hunters started the match slowly, trailing 10 - 24 in the first half, with the host putting on a dominant display. 
Paul Aiton's men started the second half on strong terms with two consecutive tries, but the home side showed resilience to seal the win with two late tries. 
The try scorers for PNG Hunters include Brendon Nima, Alex Max, Finley Glare, and Gairo Voro, with a double. 
The Hunters host Northern Pride next Sunday in Port Moresby.

snippet.description:
